<div>

  <p>This is the documentation for the IDLdoc project.</p>
  
  <p>The IDLdoc project source code can be accessed via Subversion with the command:
  <code class="listing">svn co http://svn.idldev.com/idldoc</code>
  </p>
  
  <h4>Resources</h4>
  
  <ul>
    <li><a href="http://michaelgalloy.com">Developer site</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://idldev.com">Hosting site</a></li>
  </ul>  
</div>


@dir ./ Main-level programs such as IDLdoc itself, the system object, and the version function.
@dir collection/ Collection classes (imported from mg library).
@dir dist_tools/ Routines for handling distributing applications (imported from mg library).
@dir introspection/ Routines for providing information about an IDL variable.
@dir math/ Misc computational routines (imported from mg library).
@dir parser/ Parser classes for parsing files, formats, and comments.
@dir templating/ Template class and helpers (imported from mg library).
@dir textmarkup/ Classes to convert a markup tree to a particular markup language (imported from mg library).
@dir tree/ Classes representing IDL constructs: directories, files, routines, etc.
@dir util/ Utility classes (formating integers, etc).